## Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test suite. Every production method is invoked (giving you line coverage), but almost nothing is *verified*. These tests will pass even if the production code is completely wrong.

---

### 🔴 Critical Severity

#### 1. Assertion-Free Tests (Lines 17–21, 33–35, 39–41, 64–66, 69–73, 85–88)

Six of ten tests have **zero assertions**. They exercise code paths purely to inflate coverage.

**Bugs this misses:** `AddProduct` could silently discard data, `UpdatePrice` could set the wrong value, `RemoveProduct` could be a no-op, `ApplyBulkDiscount` could corrupt prices, `ImportFromCsv` could parse incorrectly.

**Fix:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProduct()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored!.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_MakesProductUnretrievable()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}

[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_ReducesPricesByFraction()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 100m));
    _catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
    Assert.AreEqual(90m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void ImportFromCsv_CreatesProducts()
{
    _catalog.ImportFromCsv("SKU-001,Widget,9.99");
    var p = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", p!.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, p.Price);
}
```

---

#### 2. `Assert.IsNotNull` as Only Assertion (Lines 28, 51, 59, 81)

Four tests assert only non-null. A method returning a wrong product, an empty list, or garbage CSV all pass.

**Fix (examples):**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetProduct_ReturnsCorrectProduct()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    var result = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
